Meet <b>Rebecca</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Rebecca lives at <a href='/home/?user=thegreatqueen'>3222 Regal Mountain Drive</a>, in the classy area of Westridge.  She has been a citizen of Millsberry since August 29th of 2004, and continues to enjoy life in our wonderful town.<br><br>Rebecca is a very compassionate young lady, who is described as charming and friendly by her classmates at Millsberry Academy.  She is also greatly admired for her many extracurricular talents, such as her abilities as an actress and singer.  Why, just last week Rebecca was chosen by Sam Check, the teacher who directs Millsberry Academy's Drama Club, to play the lead role in the school's upcoming musical.  Rebecca is very excited about the part, since it's sure to put her talents as both a singer and actress to the test.  Everyone, however, is confident in her abilities, and quite certain that she will perform the part admirably!<br><br>After school, Rebecca enjoys shooting hoops with her friends at the Millsberry Academy Gym.  Rebecca and her friends often bring along a boom box when they head out for the basketball court, so they can listen to rap, reggae, and pop as they play.  If you are on the court after school, just look for a girl who is often dressed in violet, pink, or light blue clothes and has a sweet smile on her face!<br><br>On the weekends and in her spare time, Rebecca enjoys hanging out at the mall with her friends, walking around and shopping for various things.  After they're done shopping, Rebecca and her friends will typically head over to the movie theater in the Downtown Entertainment Complex to catch the latest flick.<br><br>If there's nothing new playing at the movies, Rebecca can usually be found at her best friend's house, hanging out and relaxing before another exciting week at school.<br><br>Congratulations Rebecca, you are certainly deserving of being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
